00:13:07,560 --> 00:13:10,358
...since my therapist
changed my anxiety medication...

230
00:13:10,520 --> 00:13:13,034
...and I stopped caring about the blood
in my stool.

231
00:13:16,439 --> 00:13:18,270
Good story.

232
00:13:18,759 --> 00:13:22,468
-What're you drinking there? Little eggnog?
-Yes. Is there a problem?

233
00:13:22,639 --> 00:13:27,030
No, it's nice to see you enjoying
a holiday beverage. Pretty Christmasy.

234
00:13:27,199 --> 00:13:29,155
Since when is eggnog a Christmas drink?

235
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:35,080
Eggs are available all year round.
I've been known to enjoy this poolside.

236
00:13:35,519 --> 00:13:38,352
Come on, Sheldon.
You know all the Christmas stories...

237
00:13:38,519 --> 00:13:41,431
...and the carols, you've got
an eggnog mustache going on there.

238
00:13:41,599 --> 00:13:44,193
Just admit it,
you're getting a little yuletide spirit.

239
00:13:44,360 --> 00:13:48,273
Don't be silly. Christmas is a bunch of
baloney created by the tinsel industry.

240
00:13:49,360 --> 00:13:51,157
Why is this so important to you?

241
00:13:51,360 --> 00:13:55,194
I had enough crappy Christmases as a kid.
I'm tired of you sucking the joy out of them.

242
00:13:55,840 --> 00:13:59,719
-What was so bad about them?
-I grew up in a house full of crazy academics.

243
00:13:59,879 --> 00:14:03,872
Instead of leaving Santa milk and cookies,
we had to leave him a research paper.

244
00:14:05,439 --> 00:14:09,478
In the morning, you could tell he'd been
there because the paper would be graded.

245
00:14:10,759 --> 00:14:14,195
No wonder you love Christmas.
That sounds amazing.

246
00:14:14,360 --> 00:14:18,831
It wasn't amazing.
I got a C-minus four years in a row.

247
00:14:18,999 --> 00:14:21,388
I'm familiar with your work.
C-minus was your gift.

248
00:14:25,519 --> 00:14:28,829
Amy, I'm really sorry.
I didn't mean to upset you.

249
00:14:28,999 --> 00:14:32,992
It's fine. I'm used to being the girl
who never gets looked at twice.

250
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:35,116
I didn't have my first kiss until I was 22.

251
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:38,033
The guy only did it
so that I would give him back his insulin.

252
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,839
[POP MUSIC PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

253
00:14:40,999 --> 00:14:44,196
Sometimes the pancreas wants
what the pancreas wants.

254
00:14:45,680 --> 00:14:47,910
Forget it.
I don't expect you guys to understand.

255
00:14:48,080 --> 00:14:49,195
I understand.

256
00:14:49,360 --> 00:14:52,716
In seventh grade, I played spin-the-bottle
and it landed on Alina Shankar.

257
00:14:52,879 --> 00:14:56,997
She said ifl came near her,
she would break the bottle and cut me.

258
00:14:57,160 --> 00:14:58,434
You think that's bad?

259
00:14:58,600 --> 00:15:02,639
In college, I passed out at a frat party
and woke up with more clothes on.

260
00:15:07,319 --> 00:15:10,629
Sometimes I get so lonely I sit
on my left hand until it goes numb...

261
00:15:10,800 --> 00:15:15,157
...then I put it in my right hand and pretend
I'm holding hands with another person.

262
00:15:15,959 --> 00:15:17,187
I do that too.

263
00:15:18,199 --> 00:15:21,271
Sometimes the left hand tries
to cop a feel.

264
00:15:22,079 --> 00:15:23,876
And I let it.

265
00:15:26,439 --> 00:15:30,398
It's kind of nice to talk to someone who
understands what it feels like to be alone.

266
00:15:30,560 --> 00:15:31,879
It is, isn't it?

267
00:15:32,039 --> 00:15:34,348
But you're not alone anymore.
Now you've got Sheldon.

268
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:38,593
I do. And don't worry,
someday you'll have somebody too.

269
00:15:38,759 --> 00:15:43,469
Thank you. I hope she's half as lovely
and amazing as you are.

270
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:46,268
Thank you, Rajesh.

271
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:48,599
He wants me, I'm good. We can go.

272
00:15:51,279 --> 00:15:52,997
-Damn it.
PENNY: What?

273
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:56,948
Now that I know she doesn't like me,
I'm kind of into her.

274
00:15:58,400 --> 00:16:03,793
All right, I think I cracked the code
to lower the drawbridge.

275
00:16:03,959 --> 00:16:05,108
HOWARD:
Great. Let's do it.

276
00:16:10,359 --> 00:16:11,872
[PLAYING JINGLE BELLS]

277
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,268
The drawbridge is lowering.

278
00:16:19,600 --> 00:16:22,194
-My carpal tunnel's acting up.
-Play through the pain.

279
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:34,838
You did it. The drawbridge is down.

280
00:16:34,999 --> 00:16:39,151
You cross the chasm
and find yourself in a small dungeon room.

281
00:16:39,319 --> 00:16:43,995
And in the corner, chained to the wall,
you see a bloodied and beaten Santa Claus.

282
00:16:44,159 --> 00:16:47,629
He says, "Ho, ho, help me."

283
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:51,839
Yes, we found Santa. Christmas is saved.

284
00:16:51,999 --> 00:16:54,388
Don't ever tell my mother I said that.

285
00:16:55,759 --> 00:16:58,956
I take out my skeleton key
and run to Santa to unchain him.

286
00:16:59,120 --> 00:17:02,635
But first I cast a spell of paralysis
on Stuart and Howard.

287
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:05,030
-What are you doing?
-Can't talk, you're paralyzed.

288
00:17:06,079 --> 00:17:09,037
I get right up in Santa's big, fat face
and say:

289
00:17:09,199 --> 00:17:13,511
"Well, well, well, Jolly old Saint Nick,
we meet again.

290
00:17:13,679 --> 00:17:17,911
I believe the last time we spoke was
in the Baybrook Mall in Galveston, Texas...

291
00:17:18,080 --> 00:17:20,150
...when l was 5 years old, isn't that right?"

292
00:17:20,319 --> 00:17:22,275
Okay.

293
00:17:22,439 --> 00:17:25,192
My mother dragged me there
and plopped me down on your lap...

294
00:17:25,360 --> 00:17:27,635
...and you asked me
what I wanted for Christmas.

295
00:17:27,799 --> 00:17:32,077
I told you my Pop-Pop, because
that was the year my grandfather died.

296
00:17:32,240 --> 00:17:34,515
I missed him and lwanted him back.

297
00:17:36,279 --> 00:17:37,758
This is weird, right?

298
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:44,438
Pop-Pop was the only one in my family
who encouraged me to pursue science.

299
00:17:44,599 --> 00:17:46,510
But you didn't bring him back, did you?

300
00:17:46,679 --> 00:17:49,352
No. Instead, I got Lincoln Logs.

301
00:17:49,520 --> 00:17:52,717
Now, you can build a lot of neat things
out of Lincoln Logs...

302
00:17:52,880 --> 00:17:54,791
...but Pop-Pop ain't one of them.

303
00:17:54,959 --> 00:17:59,237
And now you're here asking me
for something. To save you.

304
00:17:59,400 --> 00:18:03,154
Well, sorry, Mr. Kringle.
But today's not your day.

305
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:07,438
I'm leaving you here to rot
and I hope the ogres feast on your bones.

306
00:18:07,599 --> 00:18:10,875
I take the skeleton key,
toss it into the chasm...

307
00:18:11,039 --> 00:18:15,396
...and on the way out give Santa a swift kick
in his bowl full ofjelly.

308
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:19,392
Okay.

309
00:18:19,559 --> 00:18:22,232
So Wolowitz and Stuart are paralyzed,
Santa's dead...

310
00:18:22,400 --> 00:18:25,392
...and I picked this over having sex
with my girlfriend.

311
00:18:40,439 --> 00:18:44,398
-Santa?
-Oh, hello, Sheldon.

312
00:18:44,559 --> 00:18:45,548
[BELLS JINGLING]

313
00:18:45,720 --> 00:18:47,631
You should be asleep.

314
00:18:47,799 --> 00:18:50,632
Well, then you shouldn't have jingle bells
on your boots.

315
00:18:52,039 --> 00:18:53,757
I've been wanting to talk to you.

316
00:18:53,959 --> 00:18:57,998
I'm sorry I disappointed you
when you were a little boy.

317
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,036
I can do a lot of magical things...

318
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:06,637
...but unfortunately bringing
your Pop-Pop back isn't one of them.

319
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:12,712
-I understand.
-But I do have something special for you.

320
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:15,193
Close your eyes.

321
00:19:17,279 --> 00:19:19,509
Oh, I hope it's a train.

322
00:19:19,679 --> 00:19:22,637
Oh, it's better than a train.

323
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:25,676
Two trains?

324
00:19:26,360 --> 00:19:27,349
Better.

325
00:19:27,559 --> 00:19:33,031
-l'm getting three trains.
-Okay, open them.

326
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:41,518
This is for leaving me in the dungeon
to be eaten alive by ogres.

327
00:19:41,679 --> 00:19:43,749
Now, hang on. In my defense--

328
00:19:43,919 --> 00:19:46,638
Ho, ho, ho, you big dork.

329
00:19:47,439 --> 00:19:48,428
[GASPS]

330
00:20:18,039 --> 00:20:20,030
[English - us - an]

